                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id="a1">
                        <locus target="#155v" facs="158"> f. 155v, column 1, lines 15 and following</locus>
                        <locus target="#156r" facs="158"> f. 156r, (lower part)</locus>
                      <desc type="Excerpt">excerpt from <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2891RepCh172">Malkəʾa Māryām</title></desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a2">
                        <locus target="#156r" facs="158"> f. 156r, upper</locus>
                        <desc type="Asmat">Asmat prayer for safety in travel, based on <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur#59">Ps 59:1-2</title>
                      <q><foreign xml:lang="gez">
                        የቆጠጢና፡ ስር፡ ሰኞ፡ በ፱፡ ጥላ፡ ምሰህ፡ ማሰደር፡ ማክሰኞ፡ በዘጠኝ፡ ጥላ፡ ንቀል፡ ባረብ፡ ሰፍተህ፡ ያዝ፡ ምንገድ፡ ሲህዱ፡<gap reason="omitted"/>አድኅነኒ፡ እግዚኦ፡ እምጸርየ፡ መሐመድ፡ ወአንግፈኒ፡ እምእለ፡ ቆሙ፡ ላዕሌየ፡ አሕመድ፡<gap reason="omitted"/>
                      </foreign>
                      “Take the root of a plant, first dig out the ground on Monday. On Tuesday when the shadow is at 9, cut the root. Sew the root onto Moroccan leather. When you travel, take seven small stones and stand upon a big boulder and recite ‘O Lord, Save me from my enemy, Mohammad; and rescue me from the one who stands before me, Ahmed. Save me from the works of the sinner, Sayid. And save me from blood, Allah Achbar.’ Recite ‘Allah Achbar’ seven times in four directions. Throw one stone in each direction; keep the three stones with your mantle.”</q>
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a3">
                        <locus target="#157v" facs="160"> f. 157v, col. 1, top seven lines</locus>
                      <desc>Prayer Against the Tongue of People <foreign xml:lang="gez">ልሳነ፡ ሰብእ፡</foreign>, beginning <q><foreign xml:lang="gez">ስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡<gap reason="omitted"/>ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ ልሳነ፡ ሰብእ፡ ምቀኛ፡ ወተንኮለኛ፡<gap reason="omitted"/></foreign></q></desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a4">
                        <locus target="#157v" facs="160"> f. 157v, bottom of column one–column two</locus>
                      <desc type="Asmat">Repeat of Asmat prayer for protection in travel, in the top nine lines of <locus target="#156r" facs="158"/>, written in a later hand in blue ink</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a5">
                        <locus target="#158r" facs="160"/>
                      <desc type="Excerpt">(except for last three lines of the second column): Excerpt from <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2736RepCh20">Malkǝʾa Śǝllāse</title>, mixed with excerpts from <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1113Anqasa">ʾAnqaṣa bǝrhān</title>, written by a later hand in blue ink</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a6">
                        <locus target="#158r #158v #155v" facs="160 161 158"> f. 158r, col. 2, bottom three lines through to 158v, and 155v column 1, the 15 lines in blue ink</locus>
                      <desc>Excerpt from Petition and Supplication, Sǝ’ǝlät wa-‘äsǝtäbqu‘otat, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ስእለት፡ ወአስተብቍዖት፡</foreign>, written by a later hand in blue ink</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e1">
                        <locus target="#ir(ecto) #iv(erso) #iiv(erso) #157r #159r #160r #160v" facs="001 002 003 159 161 162 163"/>
                      <desc>blank except for scrawls</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a7">
                        <locus target="#iir(ecto)" facs="002"/>
                      <desc>Note of certification: <q>“If someone wants to read or recite this Psalter, it is corrected properly"
                      <foreign xml:lang="gez">አሁን፡ ግን፡ ይህነን፡ ዳዊት፡ የደገመ፡ ሰው፡ በደ(ም)በኛ፡ ሁኖ፡ ታርሟል፡ ዕዩ፡</foreign></q></desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a8">
                        <locus target="#159v" facs="162"/>
                      <desc type="Asmat">Asmat prayer for success in argument in court, in a later hand,
                      <q><foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰላም፡ ለምድር፡ ዳእደ፡ በድጋጼ፡ ምድር፡ ትረደ፡ ዘካራን፡ ዘካራን፡ ዘካራን፡ አጥባቄን፡ (አጥማቂ?)፡ ዮሀንስ፡ ረዳኤ፡ ጊዎርጊስ፡ (sic)<gap reason="omitted"/></foreign></q></desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a9">
                        <locus target="#156v" facs="159"/>
                      <desc>(17 lines): Will of Wäyzäro Kǝbitu</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e3">
                      <desc>Numbered quires: quires 1–13</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e4">
                        <locus target="#1v #33v #34v #36r #36v" facs="004 036 037 039"/>
                        <desc>etc., words of text are written interlinearly</desc>
                        </item>
                      <item xml:id="e5">
                        <locus target="#10r #39r #49v #50v #60r" facs="010 039 052 062"/>
                        <desc>etc., and lines of text are written interlinearly</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e6">
                        <locus target="#48v" facs="051"> f.48v, line 16</locus>
                        <locus target="#58r" facs="060"> f.58r, line 19</locus>
                        <desc>lines of text are written in the upper margin with a symbol (+), and in another case where the symbol (┴) marking the location where the text is to be inserted</desc>
                        </item>
                      <item xml:id="e7">
                        <locus target="#16v #82r" facs="019 084"/>
                        <desc>erasure markings are visible</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e8">
                        <locus target="#14r #38r #134r" facs="016 040 136"/>)
                        <desc>e.g., text has been removed</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e9">
                      <desc>
                      The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an
                      appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the
                      scribe completes the line of text above or below the end of the line (throughout)
                      </desc>
                      </item>
